definition: state official or subject in dynastic China/I, your servant (used in addressing the sovereign)/Kangxi radical 131

sentences.english: Potiphar, an officer of Pharaoh's, the captain of the guard, an Egyptian.
sentences.chinese: 有個埃及人普提法爾，是法郎的內臣兼衛隊長。

sentences.english: Meanwhile the Midianites had sold him in Egypt to Potiphar, an official of Pharaoh, the captain of the guard.
sentences.chinese: 米甸人在埃及把約瑟賣給法老的內臣，護衛長波提乏。
